\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li0\ri0\fi0\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 {\f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 30.} On the basis of the matters discussed above, I prefer Chan's account to that of Tsang SC concerning the newspaper advertisement, the interview, the circumstances under which Chan was offered his job, and the terms and conditions of his employment. These factors alone suggest that BQIH rather than SLY was the employer of Chan at all material times.\par}

