}

\par}

\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li0\ri0\fi0\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 {\f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 81.} I have already found earlier that the defence witnesses, in particular Tsang SC and Liao EH, were evasive, unreliable and could not be trusted. Upon a close analysis of the evidence given by Chan about the Accident, I find Chan's story regarding the Accident coherent and logical. I, therefore, prefer Chan's account of the events to the story given by the two defence witnesses of Tsang SC and Liao EH.\par}

\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li0\ri0\fi0\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 {\f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 82.} It is my finding that:- {\par}{\pard \fi-360 \li720 \ls122 
